## üîê SECURITY CHECKLIST COMPLETO

### **Pre-Audit Checklist**

#### **Access Control**
- [ ] All privileged functions have appropriate access modifiers
- [ ] Role-based access control implemented correctly
- [ ] Owner cannot rug pull user funds
- [ ] Time-locks on critical admin functions

#### **Reentrancy Protection**
- [ ] All external calls use ReentrancyGuard
- [ ] Checks-Effects-Interactions pattern followed
- [ ] No state changes after external calls

#### **Input Validation**
- [ ] All user inputs validated
- [ ] Array bounds checked
- [ ] Zero address checks
- [ ] Minimum/maximum value checks

#### **Integer Safety**
- [ ] Using Solidity 0.8.x built-in overflow checks
- [ ] No unsafe casts
- [ ] Division by zero protected

#### **External Calls**
- [ ] All external calls have try-catch
- [ ] Return values checked
- [ ] Reentrancy protected
- [ ] Gas limits considered

#### **Oracle Security (Chainlink)**
- [ ] VRF subscription properly funded
- [ ] RequestId properly tracked
- [ ] Callback function secured (onlyVRFCoordinator)
- [ ] No manipulation of randomness

#### **Gas Optimization**
- [ ] Loops bounded or paginated
- [ ] Storage vs memory optimized
- [ ] Unnecessary storage reads minimized
- [ ] Events used instead of storage where possible

#### **Upgradability (if applicable)**
- [ ] Storage layout preserved
- [ ] Initializers protected
- [ ] No selfdestruct in implementation

#### **Testing Coverage**
- [ ] Unit tests >80% coverage
- [ ] Integration tests for critical paths
- [ ] Edge cases tested
- [ ] Failure scenarios tested

---

## üìä SUCCESS METRICS & KPIs

### **Technical Metrics**
- [ ] 5+ modalidades funcionales
- [ ] 90%+ test coverage
