Main Focus
This hackathon explores self-service banking on Bitcoin rails, all powered by Mezo.
ÔªøMezo enables users to borrow MUSD against Bitcoin collateral at 1% fixed rates, maintaining full control over their positions. Users can close positions whenever they want, add collateral as needed, and deploy their MUSD across DeFi to earn yield that covers their borrowing costs.

The model is simple: Bitcoin holders deposit BTC as collateral, mint MUSD (a Bitcoin-backed stablecoin), and use it for spending or yield generation while keeping their Bitcoin exposure. Everything happens onchain and transparently - users can audit positions, track collateral ratios, and manage their own risk.

Mezo helps transform Bitcoin from static holdings into productive capital without requiring users to sell or trust intermediaries.

Requirements:
Your project must integrate MUSD
You must deploy working demo on testnet
Your project must be developed during the hackathon (original work) or present a completely new approach to an existing project
KYB needed for prize distribution
All Mezo incentives are tied to milestones and are conditional on being live on Mezo or ETH mainnet
ÔªøChoose your focus area based on your target users
Advanced DeFi Solutions - For degens, and institutions

Financial Access & Mass Adoption - For everyday users and underbanked communities

Daily Bitcoin Applications - For everyone

Judging Criteria
Mezo Integration (30%) - Effective use of MUSD
Technical Implementation (30%) - Code quality, architecture, security
Business Viability & Use Case (20%) - How aligned with the track theme, problem-solution fit, Market potential
User Experience (10%) - Design, usability, accessibility
ÔªøPresentation Quality (10%) - Demo clarity, pitch effectiveness
Bonus: Huge plus for projects that want to pursue their development further

